{{Infobox protected area | name = Benjamin Rush State Park | iucn_category = III <!-- images --> | photo = BRSP Community Garden.jpg | photo_caption = A small plot in the community gardens of Benjamin Rush State Park <!-- map --> | map = USA Pennsylvania | map_image = | map_size = | map_caption = Location of Benjamin Rush State Park in Pennsylvania | relief = <!-- location --> | location = [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania|Philadelphia]], [[Philadelphia County, Pennsylvania|Philadelphia]], Pennsylvania, United States | nearest_city = | nearest_town = | coordinates = {{coord|40|07|10|N|74|58|36|W|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = <!-- stats --> | length = | length_mi = | length_km = | width = | width_mi = | width_km = | area_acre = 275 | area_ref = | elevation = {{convert|118|ft|m|abbr=on}} | elevation_avg = | elevation_min = | elevation_max = | dimensions = | designation = <!-- dates & info --> | authorized = | created = | designated = | established = 1975 | named_for = [[Benjamin Rush]] | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_ref = | governing_body = Pennsylvania Department of Conservation and Natural Resources | administrator = | operator = | owner = <!-- website, embedded --> | website = [http://www.dcnr.state.pa.us/stateparks/findapark/benjaminrush/index.htm Benjamin Rush State Park] | embedded = }} '''Benjamin Rush State Park''' is a {{convert|275|acre|adj=on}} [[List of Pennsylvania state parks|Pennsylvania state park]] in [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania|Philadelphia]], [[Philadelphia County, Pennsylvania|Philadelphia County]], [[Pennsylvania]], in the United States. The park is undeveloped and is the site of community [[garden]]s, believed to be one of the largest in the world. The park is home to the Northeast Radio Controlled Airplane Club. Benjamin Rush State Park is in [[Northeast Philadelphia]] at the intersection of Southampton Road and Roosevelt Boulevard ([[U.S. Route 1]]).<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.dcnr.state.pa.us/stateparks/findapark/benjaminrush/index.htm | title = Benjamin Rush State Park Official Web Site | accessdate = 2006-11-16 | publisher = Pennsylvania Department of Conservation and Natural Resources}}</ref><ref> {{ cite web|url=http://www.phillyfunguide.com/organization.php?id=118 |title=Benjamin Rush State Park |accessdate=2006-12-07 |publisher=Greater Philadelphia Cultural Alliance |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061021165032/http://www.phillyfunguide.com/organization.php?id=118 |archivedate=2006-10-21 |df= }}</ref> The northern boundary of the park is formed by [[Poquessing Creek]]. There are several acres of woodlands along the creek bank. A proposal map show plans to connect the park with [[Fairmount Park]].<ref name="proposal"/> Other proposed improvements included hiking trails, parking facilities, and a [[reforestation]] project. The community gardens and airfield for the [[radio-controlled aircraft]] would remain.<ref name="proposal">{{cite map | url = http://www.dcnr.state.pa.us/ucmprd1/groups/public/documents/document/dcnr_005145.pdf | format = pdf | title = Benjamin Rush State Park revised development plan | publisher = Pennsylvania Department of Conservation and Natural Resources | date = August 25, 2009 | accessdate = November 30, 2011}}</ref>
