{{Infobox Museum |name = National Museum of Natural History at the National Academy of Sciences of Ukraine |native_name = Національний науково-природничий музей НАН України |native_name_lang = uk |image = P1400296-001.JPG |imagesize = 250 px |established = 1966 (08.06.1966) |location = 15 Bohdan Khmelnitsky ([[Kiev Metro|M.]]&nbsp;"Teatralna"), [[Kyiv]], 01030, [[Ukraine]] |coordinates = {{Coord|50|26|43|N|30|30|53|E|display=inline}} |architect = |visitors = ~ 100,000 |director = Igor Yemelyanov |curator = |website = [http://museumkiev.org/indexeng.html www.museumkiev.org] }} '''National Museum of Natural History at the National Academy of Sciences of Ukraine''' ({{lang-uk|Національний науково-природничий музей НАН України}}) is a [[natural history museum]] in the Ukrainian capital Kyiv. It is one of the biggest scientific research museums of the type in the world<ref name="museumkiev">{{cite web | url=http://museumkiev.org/indexeng.html | title=National Museum of Natural History | date= | accessdate=January 20, 2018}}</ref>
== History of the museum == The museum is housed in a former Olgynska school built in 1914–1927 in neoclassicism style<ref>Памятники истории и культуры Украинской ССР. – К.: 1987 г., с. 30 {{ref-ru}}</ref>. It was granted the status of the National Museum of December 10, 1996, according to the decision of the [[President of Ukraine]]<ref name="museumkiev"/>.
== Structure of display == It was established in 1966 as a unified complex comprising five museums: the Geological, Paleontological, Zoological, Botanical and Archaeological. There are approximately 30,000 [[Exhibit (educational)|exhibits]] in 24 halls with a total area of 8,000 m². The museum is open from Wednesday to Sunday from 10&nbsp;am to 5&nbsp;pm<ref name="museumkiev"/>.
== Proceedings == The museum publishes two annual journals: * [[Proceedings of the National Museum of Natural History]] ISSN: 2219—7516 (Print) : editor-in-chief: [[Igor Yemelyanov]] * [[Proceedings of the Theriological School]] ISSN 2312—2749 (Print) • ISSN 2074—2274 (Online) : editor-in-chief: [[Igor Zagorodniuk]]
